Daemon sets.

Daemon Sets ensure that every single node in the kubernetes cluster runs the same pod resource.
- Useful if you want to ensure that a certain pod is running on every single kubernetes nodePort

When a node is added to the cluster  a new pod will be started automatically.

With a node is removed the pod will not be rescheduled on another node.

use cases:

-loggining
-monitoring
-load balancers /reverse proxies / API Gateways.

A running a daemon that only needs pod instance per physical instance.
